<HL>
   CBI Industries Sets Redemption
</HL>
<DATE>
08/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12
</SO>
<CO>
   CBH
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   OAK BROOK, Ill. -- CBI Industries Inc. said it is calling
for the redemption of its $85.4 million outstanding of 7%
convertible subordinated debentures due Oct. 30, 2011.
   The construction concern said the debentures will be
redeemed at $52.45 for each $50 principal amount plus accrued
and unpaid interest, for a total redemption price of $53.62.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   CBI said the debentures are convertible into its common at
$34 a share, or 1.471 shares for each $50 principal amount.
   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange
yesterday, CBI closed at $41, down $1.125.
   If the debentures are fully converted into common, CBI
said, it will issue about 2.5 million shares. As of July 31,
CBI had 19.5 million common shares outstanding. CBI said
conversion rights expire at 3 p.m. EDT Aug. 31.
</TEXT>
